para_trans: Sub-Registrar, Co-operative Societies Group-A under probation appointed by direct service in 2011
Department of Cooperation, Marketing and Textiles,
Madam Cama Marg, Martyrdom Rajguru Chowk,
Read: Government Decision No. Rajas 1011 / PR No. 292/5 S, D. 31/5/2012
Reference No. A total of 12 candidates are being examined under 1 Sub-Registrar, Cooperative Societies.
Group A has been appointed for a period of two years. The following have satisfactorily completed the two-year probationary period as per the terms of the aforesaid appointment order:
The probationary period of the officers expires on the date indicated before their names.
The government has decided to do it. Hence, from this date onwards, the present officers are being given regular appointments to their posts.
2. The Commissioner and Registrar of Cooperatives, Cooperative Societies, Maharashtra State, Pune to inform the concerned.
Action should be taken to take appropriate notes in the service book of the aforesaid officers.
This Government decision is available on the website of the Government of Maharashtra www.maharashtra.gov.in.
